title: Enterobacter sp. RHBSTW-00422 chromosome, complete genome
isolation_source: Freshwater sample from downstream of wastewater treatment plant
bioproject_description: NCBI has developed an automatic annotation pipeline that combines ab initio gene prediction algorithms with homology based methods. See more details here. Annotation from different submitters varies in quality resulting in the inconsistent annotation even in closely related genomes. The NCBI Prokaryotic Annotation Pipeline can produce consistent high quality automatic annotation.

title: Phaseolus vulgaris isolate INB_841 ecotype Mesoamerican chromosome 1, whole genome shotgun sequence
bioproject_description: INB_841 is an interspecific breeding line derived from Phaseolus acutifolius. It exhibits several beneficial agronomic traits, including drought tolerance. A de novo genome assembly and annotation of this line are of particular relevance, as they provide a foundation for the informed exploration and use of the exotic genetic diversity it carries
